&lt;h2 id="the-grammar-of-entropy">&lt;em>The Grammar of Entropy&lt;/em>&lt;/h2>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>“**But entropy, heat, past and future are qualities that belong not to the fundamental grammar of the world but to our superficial observation of it. ‘If I observe the microscopic state of things,’ writes Rovelli, ‘then the difference between past and future vanishes … in the elementary grammar of things, there is no distinction between “cause” and “effect””**1&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>